### 3. Limpeza de Tipagem — Prioridade Baixa

#### [MODIFY] [charger.ts](file:///c:/Users/jonathan-moletta/.gemini/antigravity/playground/tensor-aurora/web/src/types/charger.ts) (linhas 32-38)

Remover campos duplicados `snake_case`, mantendo apenas `camelCase`:
```diff
 export interface OperationSettings {
   businessStart?: string;
   businessEnd?: string;
   workOnWeekends?: boolean;
-  business_start?: string;
-  business_end?: string;
-  work_on_weekends?: boolean;
 }
```

#### [MODIFY] [page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/jonathan-moletta/.gemini/antigravity/playground/tensor-aurora/web/src/app/%5Bcontext%5D/gestao-carregadores/page.tsx) (linhas 65-66)

Remover fallbacks snake_case no cálculo de `isInBusinessHours`:
```diff
-const bStart = parseInt(settings?.businessStart?.split(":")[0] || settings?.business_start?.split(":")[0] || "8", 10);
-const bEnd = parseInt(settings?.businessEnd?.split(":")[0] || settings?.business_end?.split(":")[0] || "18", 10);
+const bStart = parseInt(settings?.businessStart?.split(":")[0] || "8", 10);
+const bEnd = parseInt(settings?.businessEnd?.split(":")[0] || "18", 10);
```

O [chargerService.ts](file:///c:/Users/jonathan-moletta/.gemini/antigravity/playground/tensor-aurora/web/src/lib/api/chargerService.ts) já mapeia `business_start` → `businessStart` no [fetchGlobalSchedule()](file:///c:/Users/jonathan-moletta/.gemini/antigravity/playground/tensor-aurora/web/src/lib/api/chargerService.ts#65-80) (linha 74-78), então o frontend sempre recebe camelCase.

